timelimit
------------------------------------------
timelimit executes a command and terminates the spawned process after a given
time with a given signal. A 'warning' signal is sent first, then, after a
timeout, a 'kill' signal, similar to the way init(8) operates on shutdown.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.14-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.22.51-2
  cygport-0.10.10-1
  gcc4-core-4.5.3-3
  make-3.82.90-1

Canonical website:
  http://devel.ringlet.net/sysutils/timelimit/

Canonical download:
  http://devel.ringlet.net/sysutils/timelimit/timelimit-1.8.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack timelimit-1.8-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./timelimit-1.8-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/timelimit-1.8-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/timelimit-1.8-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(timelimit)
  /usr/bin/timelimit.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/timelimit.README
  /usr/share/doc/timelimit/NEWS
  /usr/share/man/man1/timelimit.1.gz

------------------

